President Bush spoke at a memorial service held at Virginia Tech for the victims of the April 16 shooting rampage that killed 32 people, including the gunman. 
 Bush described the day as a day of mourning for the Virginia Tech community and for the entire nation. 
 "This is a day of mourning for the Virginia Tech community and it is a day of sadness for our entire nation," Bush said. 
